---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service | Quoter"
  description="Terms for roofers using Quoter on their website."
>
  <main class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-20 sm:py-24">
    <div class="legal-panel rounded-3xl p-7 sm:p-10">
      <a href="/" class="text-[14px] font-medium text-brand-600 hover:underline">&larr; Back to Quoter</a>

      <h1 class="font-display mt-5 text-[clamp(1.9rem,5vw,2.6rem)] leading-[1.05] text-ink">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[13px] text-muted">Last updated: July 2026</p>

      <h2>What Quoter is</h2>
      <p>
        Quoter is a tool for roofing businesses. You put it on your website so
        visitors can type an address and see an estimated price for roofing
        work. Quoter uses satellite imagery to measure the roof and return a
        price range for that property.
      </p>

      <h2>Who these terms cover</h2>
      <p>
        These terms apply to roofers and contractors who use Quoter on their
        sites, and to anyone who uses a Quoter estimate widget. If you embed
        Quoter, you are responsible for how it appears on your site and for
        the way you follow up with customers who use it.
      </p>

      <h2>Estimates are not final quotes</h2>
      <p>
        Every price Quoter shows is a ballpark figure to help a customer plan
        and to help you qualify leads. It is not a contract, an offer, or a
        final price. You or your team confirm the exact price after you
        inspect the property. Only that confirmed price counts.
      </p>

      <h2>Using Quoter</h2>
      <p>
        Quoter is free to try. You agree not to misuse the service, attempt to
        break it, scrape it at scale, or use it in a way that harms other
        users. You agree to only promote Quoter estimates for jobs you are
        willing and able to follow up on in good faith.
      </p>

      <h2>Accuracy</h2>
      <p>
        We work to make estimates useful, but satellite measurements and
        regional pricing have limits. We cannot guarantee accuracy. We are not
        responsible for business or hiring decisions made on an estimate alone.
      </p>

      <h2>Your content and branding</h2>
      <p>
        When you embed Quoter, you may show it alongside your own branding.
        You keep ownership of your site and brand. You give us permission to
        run the estimate service on the pages where you place the widget.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:hello@quoter.app" class="text-brand-600 hover:underline">hello@quoter.app</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-panel {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.86);
    backdrop-filter: blur(20px) saturate(1.3);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(20px) saturate(1.3);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-float);
  }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 19px;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin-top: 1.9rem;
  }
  p {
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
  }
</style>
